MODIFICATION SUMMARY

All third-party components listed above have been modified through package
relocation (also known as "shading" or "shadowing") using the Gradle Shadow
plugin. This process rewrites bytecode to change package names and update all
references, allowing multiple versions of the same library to coexist without
conflicts.

The modifications are limited to:
1. Package namespace changes (adding cx.smile. prefix)
2. Bytecode constant pool updates to reflect new package names
3. Internal reference updates to maintain functionality

No functional changes, feature additions, or bug fixes have been made to the
original library code beyond the package relocation.

This distribution bundles all components into a single Android AAR file for
convenient deployment.
